dogecoin.text: @og_dogecoin Just my 2 cents. Which is worth exactly that.

@og_dogecoin Most people that bought today will wait to see what happens tomorrow before they sell, IMO. Also, many people know that if Coinbase decides to take DOGE, DOGE will triple in an hour. So they'll wait on that decision. At least for a while.
@og_dogecoin There are definitely a lot of big buys (pumps) right now, but I think the constant flow of new buyers today has helped stem the pressure to drive the price down.

@og_dogecoin Everyone wishes they'd bought Bitcoin at $0.09. They just signed up for RH and saw BTC at 63K and DOGE at $0.09. RH only has 5 coins, which gives DOGE the perception of credibility, so they buy it as a low-risk option in case it grows like crazy.

@og_dogecoin I think many people are deciding to try crypto for the first time today. While many risk-takers and early-adopters will sign up for coinbase, many will go for the "safer" Robinhood option. And DOGE is the only one there with an early-FOMO upside potential.

@og_dogecoin I don't think it'll go "to the moon" today, but I don't think it'll drop a ton, either. I think this is just the build-up to the Coinbase IPO. Even though DOGE isn't on there yet, it is the most accessible of the sub-dollar coins, so it is benefitting from the overall attention
